CSS Selectors(Cascading Styling Sheet)

It is another way to locate an element uniquely
Syntax:
tagname[attribute = 'attribute value']
Example: button[type = 'submit']
CSs does not give you an opportunity ot identify an element by text
Shortcuts for css:
    Shortcut for className:
    tagName.classNameValue
    Example: input.nav-input

    Shortcut of ID: '#' -- ID
    tagname#IDvalue
    Example: input#twotabsearchtextbox

contains() method in css:
*symbol represents contains() method -- tagname[attribute *= 'containing attribute value']
Example: span[class *= 'form']

starts-with method in css:
^ symbol represents starts-with method -- tagname[attribute] ^= 'starting attribute value']
Example: input[id ^= 'btnv']

ends-with method in css:
$ symbol represent ends0with method --- tagName[atrribute $= 'ending attribute value']
Example: img[src $= 'syntax.png']